social_posts.post_text: Experimenting with higher weight ranges with my deadlifts again - I’m still gunshy from the great psoas/IT band fail of 2022 so north of 200# has been scary in a way it didn’t used to be. But here is 215#, and it’s looking like it’s going up relatively quick. Good to know. Yay @williamsburgstrengthworks for giving me the space to get my shit done.
Night 1 of @peppergrinds’ Winter Striptacular was one for the books! Tickets are almost gone for tomorrow and Sunday so grab them while they remain! And uh look at how hot I am.

Did not need to be so violently humbled by this past year (or did I?), and its attending challenges to my body and capacity. I spent more time than usual in a place of dissolution and vulnerability, the takeaway of which will benefit me in better years and along with the pleasure and joy I’ve been able to savor. If I must learn and grow -sigh- at least I’m doing so with my clothes off and surrounded by cash. Enjoy your grave, 2022, you son of a b*tch.
A cinch is a terrible thing to waist. Thank you @darkgardencorsetry for making this STUHHHHNING outfit for me to wear to @fatlesquefestnw. I feel like Hollywood royalty. Holy cats.
See how much I love my dress?
Feeling like a boss at @fatlesquefestnw. Photo by Keith Johnson, outfit by @darkgardencorsetry.

social_posts.post_text: If you have been to an ECC party then you have had the joy of seeing this talented queen perform! Fancy Feast is a Brooklyn-based burlesque performer, writer, and sex educator. She holds the title of Miss Coney Island 2016, and is the recipient of the Revolutionary Award at the 2017 New York Burlesque Festival. We could not be more excited!!! Get tickets NOW! Link in bio #neon #neonart #galleryofart #burlesque #nycburlesque #sexynight #valentines #nycqueer #nycevents #loveit #neonlove
Uhhhhh these turned out so hot??? Leather pasties with clamp chain, black and gunmetal embellishment. Phew.

Quite astonishingly and through no fault of my own, it’s my birthday and I’m now 35 years old. I feel lucky beyond belief for my life and the people in it, and thankful for new frontiers of creative expression that keep me focused on a long and joyful to do list. Excited for the year ahead. I think this is going to be a big one.
New coyote skull just dropped! Inspired by my recent trip to the Mugler exhibit for my use of mixed materials and organic lines to exaggerate the skull’s existing shapes.

TGIF, nerds. What are you looking forward to this weekend? My answer is a little tragic; rhinestoning, baby. 

This dress was a bridesmaids outfit. It’s true what they say. You can wear it again.

BOOK COVER REVEAL! I am beyond excited and overwhelmed to announce that the book I wrote is officially available for preorder. Enormous gratitude to everyone who has helped make this happen, especially my agent @connorgoldsmith, and the unbelievable team at @algonquinbooks. The link to order my book is in my bio; preordering is one of the best things you can do for a first time author so if you have $18, be one of the first to snag a copy. I’ve been writing this book on and off for eight years (eight???) and I’m ready for it to be out in the world and in your hot little hands. Also yes, I made those pasties.

COVER REVEAL & GALLEY GIVEAWAY

We’re excited to reveal the cover for NAKED by Fancy Feast! The celebrated burlesque performer, sex educator, and social worker bares it all in this incisive collection of essays (available October 10) that gives readers a backstage pass to the world of nightlife and sex work, examining our cultural hang-ups and obsessions with bodies, desire, and even love. 

Follow the instructions below to enter for a chance to win one of 10 advance copies, and pre-order via the @bookshop_org link in our bio— use the code NAKED10 at checkout for 10% off. 

“Fancy reveals how our masks are just as authentic as our flesh.” —HuffPost

Wanna know something truly wild? In ONE MONTH, the @fuckyourevue is BACK, for a show in collaboration with @jewishmuseum_md and @newjewishculture at @abronsartscenter! If you recall, the Revue’s last show was March 8, 2020… can’t imagine why it’s taken us so long to come back. But here we are, resplendent. Mark your calendars for Sunday June 4, because we have so much to show you.

Dare I say… CAST ANNOUNCEMENT! The next @fuckyourevue is on Sunday June 4, and we are collaborating with @jewishmuseum_md @newjewishculture on bringing a chosen selection of the chosen people together for an evening of Jewish drag, burlesque, and beyond. Swipe through for the incredible cast! Tickets are available through the @abronsartscenter ‘s site and is also in my bio! See you Sunday, June 4th at 7:30pm.

I’m a Jewish burlesque performer and I love getting to tell stories that center Jewish experiences, culture, and identity. My beloved coproducer @zoeziegfeld and I are putting together an all Jewish burlesque, drag, and variety show called JEWTOPIA on Sunday June 4th at the Abrons Arts Center in NYC. The cast is a veritable who’s who and I would hate for you to miss out on all the fun. Ticket link in my profile! Also, whatever, look at me.
Every now and then I look at a cast and just go, are you kidding me? That’s my feeling about the next @fuckyourevue’s lineup. See all these talented babes on Sunday, June 4 at @abronsartscenter!

Despite being an unmistakably Jewish person, I’m nevertheless ambivalent about how my Judaism is practiced. One of the few things that I continue to know about it, deep in my heart, is that exploring Jewishness through art and performance makes something that has felt broken become whole again. Sunday’s @fuckyourevue feels like it’s right on time: three years since the last edition of the show in March 2020, four years since the end of my year as a @newjewishculture fellow, seven years as a coproducer with @zoeziegfeld, and on the cusp of what I hope will be a wild new way of being. It’s going to be a don’t miss this kind of evening, and I hope to see you there. (@abronsartscenter, show at 7:30pm)
Sunday is not the Lord’s Day for us Jews which is why we are getting away with a sacrilicious good time at the @fuckyourevue this Sunday, June 4 at 7:30pm!
Photos from @fuckyourevue’s JEWTOPIA from @sidewalkkilla are blowing my mind! Swipe through for shots of the stunning cast!

You don’t want to miss this show!

The best thing about summer is spending time at @coney.island.usa!! I’m thrilled and delighted to coproduce The Unbookables with @heytigerbay — we are presenting some of the most amazing performers in NYC and their least sought after acts! This is your chance to see rarely performed, unearthed burlesque that is too niche, too weird, too messy, or too wtf to be seen by the public. 

The show is July 15 and tickets are on sale now through Coney Island USA’s website. Swipe through for a look at the incredible cast!

Ever the confrontational showgirl. 

I’ve long desired a way to pull together the kind of sleaze and entertainment that I’ve surrounded myself with the past decade with academies, respectability, and funding. I keep hoping the book is that - is a tangible translation across genres that makes this part of my world accessible to people who don’t think they have permission (yet) to explore it. 

And then there’s the inevitable question of, what happens if that works? What gets lost in translation? What is missing or reinterpreted? Was it worth it?

Questions over this morning’s coffee. Photo @__adrianbuckmaster___
On the road again! Here are some of my fall book events - where do you want to see me next?

In ONE WEEK, there will be the oh so chic pre-launch party for my book at @slipperroomny, Monday 10.9 at 7pm, with performances by @heytigerbay @darlindajust @theladyappeal, a chance to buy the first, hot off the presses copies of my book before the public release, and a dance party! It’s going to be a gag and a half and the recommended dress code is TACKY so do your worst. See you there!

Photo by Norman Blake
I guess I’m self reflective?

Today is pub day, as they call it, the day the book is published and available in the world - which means, with a measure of gratitude, that the book no longer belongs to me, if it ever did. It’s time for everyone else who finds it and reads it to have their own relationship with it, conversations that I won’t be privy to. I have achieved one of the biggest goals I have set for myself in my life thus far, which feels as strange and sad as it does feel wonderful. 

So what’s more revealing than that? 

My book is out! I’m in bed anticipating today’s press.
With a headline like that, you have to post it in the grid. Link in my stories to my interview in @interviewmag!

Find out just how unglamorous the glamorous life is! I wrote a piece for @shopspectrumboutique that delves into the public private life of sx writers - big thanks to @dirtylola for making this happen! Link in my stories.

@kristenmillares’ beautiful review of my book for @washingtonpost is out online today! She was kind enough to mention my skull collection so I figured I should post my latest. I can’t tell you how wild it feels to have my book reviewed in the newspaper I grew up reading as a young Washingtonian. Absolutely nuts. Link in my stories to the review!
It’s so crazy to see your face in the newspaper! Today I’m in the New York Post - big bad font and all! Thank you to @raquellaneri for the wonderful interview.

CAST CAST CAST!!! It’s an absolute dream to work with this amazing cavalcade of cuties for @arsnovanyc’s SHOWGASM on Thursday 11/9. Question for you as you swipe through: what theme do you think we are going for here?

Channeling a little bit of the Britney inside of me to tell you that SHOWGASM is real, SHOWGASM is nigh, and it’s going to be flipping fantastic. 

I’m hosting an edition of the variety show Showgasm at @arsnovanyc on Thursday 11/9 - tickets are a pay what you can, sliding scale to make sure the arts are accessible to all. I have a fabulous lineup of some of my very favorite performers: @daphne_always @tvmiscallaneous @garararararara @msabbyfantastic @cestquoi and lil ole me! This is one of those don’t miss evenings. Spend your Thirsty Thursday with us. Xoxo gossip girl

While Mondays may not be marvelous, our Host for the Cabaret of Lights is - Joining us all the way from New York City, It's @fancyfeastburlesque (she/her)!

Fancy Feast is a Brooklyn-based burlesque performer, writer, and sex educator. She has performed at venues including The Whitney, the Brooklyn Museum, St. Ann’s Warehouse, the Metropolitan Opera, and Meow Wolf in Santa Fe, and has been profiled in Vogue, NPR, Interview Magazine, and The Huffington Post. She is the author of Naked: On Sex, Work, and Other Burlesques (Algonquin Books, 2023).
